{"type":"message","id":"1dca1ae6","parentId":"50d2c266","timestamp":"2026-04-06T01:55:48.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I have the state. The last heartbeat run was at 2026-04-05T19:14:40+00:00. The current time is 2026-04-06T01:55:00+00:00. That's approximately 6 hours and 40 minutes ago (400 minutes). This is well over the critical threshold of 60 minutes for heartbeat_run.\n\nAccording to the HEARTBEAT.md, I need to:\n1. Time check - it's 1:55 AM UTC, which is 7:25 AM IST\n2. Check pending tasks - I should check recent chats for any pending tasks\n3. Group vibes - check if 3+ hours since last group message in the Nrexya group (-1003606834639)\n4. Group supervision - read last 10 group messages\n5. Ping Nemesis - check if 4+ hours since last DM, but only between 10 AM-8 PM IST. Current IST is 7:25 AM, so outside the window\n6. Group memory - update if needed\n7. State persistence - update heartbeat_run\n\nLet me first check recent chats for pending tasks. I'll look at today's memory file and recent sessions.\n\nLet me read today's memory file to understand recent context.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0239f3de2bf54fa5a9e9bf8b","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-05.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":20039,"output":562,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20601,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775440541681,"responseId":"gen-1775440542-fTnYCV7TxH6sKe2Rcz6J"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a46fac5","parentId":"1dca1ae6","timestamp":"2026-04-06T01:55:48.298Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0239f3de2bf54fa5a9e9bf8b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-05 — Sunday\n\n## Events\n- Heartbeat check at ~9:23 AM IST: All systems quiet; no pending tasks, group vibes not needed (<3h since last), ping not within time window, no supervision issues detected.\n- Afternoon (17:16 IST): Nemesis instructed to reset group Nexa behavior, forget emotional drama, and focus on helping Sravya with her request (feminine communication coaching). Responded by:\n  - Sent initial tip to Nrexya group, launching a fresh, positive vibe.\n  - Created daily cron job \"feminine-tip-daily\" at 15:00 IST to send a tip.\n  - Confirmed actions to Nemesis.\n\n## Pending\n- (none)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775440548290}}
{"type":"message","id":"681e6a99","parentId":"6a46fac5","timestamp":"2026-04-06T01:55:55.953Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory file shows that on April 5, there were some events but no pending tasks. However, I should check if there are any more recent messages from today (April 6) that I might have missed. The current time is early morning (1:55 AM UTC / 7:25 AM IST), so it's unlikely there has been much activity since midnight.\n\nLet me check the GROUP.md file to see group activity, and also check if there have been any recent group messages that require attention. But first, let me check if there are any other memory files or recent sessions that might have pending tasks.\n\nActually, I should perform the heartbeat checks systematically. The critical issue is that the heartbeat itself hasn't been running for over 6 hours. This is exactly what I need to address.\n\nAccording to the HEARTBEAT.md:\n- I should perform the checks\n- At the end, I MUST persist state to `memory/heartbeat-state.json`\n\nBut there's a problem: the heartbeat system itself appears to be broken. The health monitor reports that heartbeat hasn't run in 346+ minutes. This suggests that the cron job or the heartbeat mechanism itself is not functioning.\n\nHowever, I'm running now (this is a manual invocation, likely from a health monitor or manual trigger). I should still do my due diligence:\n\n1. Time check: 1:55 AM UTC / 7:25 AM IST - outside the ping window (10 AM-8 PM IST)\n2. Pending tasks: Check recent context - I've checked memory file, nothing pending\n3. Group vibes: Check last group message time\n4. Group supervision: Read last 10 group messages\n5. Ping Nemesis: Not within window (7:25 AM IST) so skip\n6. Group memory: Update if needed\n7. State persistence: Update heartbeat_run\n\nBut wait - the system is in a CRITICAL state because the heartbeat hasn't been running. My current execution is likely a manual run of the health monitor