{"type":"message","id":"1a501a7d","parentId":"321d3848","timestamp":"2026-04-06T01:56:34.872Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"crontab is not available. Maybe it's in a different location or the system uses a different mechanism. I can check /etc/crontab or /var/spool/cron/crontabs. But I might not have permission.\n\nAlternatively, I could check the openclaw configuration for cron jobs. The health monitor says there are cron jobs and lists them. Maybe they're managed by OpenClaw's own scheduler, not system cron.\n\nGiven the constraints, I'll focus on what I can do: I'll update the state file to mark that a heartbeat check occurred now. This will at least reset the staleness for this run and allow the health monitor to not flag it as stale for the next cycle, assuming the cron continues to run. But if the heartbeat cron itself is broken, the state won't update again until next manual run.\n\nI'll also try to see if I can identify why the heartbeat hasn't been running. Perhaps I can look at logs. But the instructions say: Do not infer or repeat old tasks. I should just do the heartbeat checklist.\n\nLet's proceed to update the state. I'll also check if I should send any alert. The ping window is closed, and I can't send due to time window anyway. So I will not send any message.\n\nNow, state persistence: I need to run the Python script to update heartbeat_run. The script is at: ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/heartbeat-state-manager/scripts/update_state.py\n\nLet me call it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_623388605f8144f09735a59c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/heartbeat-state-manager/scripts/update_state.py --field heartbeat_run"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":1902,"output":714,"cacheRead":22784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25400,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cache