{"type":"message","id":"6f3fcd61","parentId":"b39dcba6","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:55:39.799Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is sending another heartbeat prompt. I need to follow the HEARTBEAT.md checklist strictly and check if anything needs attention. Let me evaluate:\n\nCurrent time: Monday, April 6th, 2026 — 6:55 AM (UTC)\n\nFrom the HEARTBEAT.md checklist:\n1. Time check first: Get the current IST time. Note it.\n2. Pending tasks: If Nemesis mentioned a pending task in recent chats, check if there's anything to follow up on.\n3. Group vibes: Check if it's been 3+ hours since the last group message (-1003606834639). ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context. Do not send empty 'just saying hi' messages. Skip entirely after 11 PM IST.\n4. Group supervision: Read last 10 group messages. If the group Nexa said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis, send a correction to the group.\n5. Ping Nemesis: Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). ONLY ping Nemesis if there is a relevant alert, a pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests. Do not send forced casual chatter.\n6. Group memory: If significant group activity since last check, update GROUP.md.\n7. Silent Execution: Execute background tasks (like updating GROUP.md) silently. Do not DM Nemesis just to report that a task was completed.\n8. Exit Protocol: If no tasks require attention and no alerts are needed, send absolutely NOTHING. Execute a silent exit.\n\nState Persistence: After completing all checks, ALWAYS persist state to `memory/heartbeat-state.json`.\n\nLet me check the current state:\n- Current UTC time: 6:55 AM\n- IST time: UTC+5:30 = 12:25 PM IST (6:55 + 5:30 = 12:25)\n\nNow I need to check:\n- Last group message time from GROUP.md or state\n- Last DM to/from Nemesis\n\n\nI'll start by examining the heartbeat state file to gather