{"type":"message","id":"044d5649","parentId":"1e224b69","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:56:20.703Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the current state:\n\nCurrent time: 2026-04-06 06:55 UTC\n\n- heartbeat_run: last at 06:26:27 UTC → ~28 minutes ago → OK (threshold 60 min)\n- group_message: last at 2026-04-05T19:14:40 UTC → ~11h 40m ago → Check threshold: warning ≥4h, critical ≥6h → This is >6h, so CRITICAL for group_message\n- nemesis_ping: last at 2026-04-06T04:28:03 UTC → ~2h 27m ago → Check threshold: warning ≥6h, critical ≥8h → OK (within 10 AM-8 PM IST window? It's 12:25 PM IST now, so within window but not enough time passed)\n- git_push: last at 2026-04-05T19:14:40 UTC → ~11h 40m ago → warning ≥3h, critical ≥6h → CRITICAL (since >6h)\n- memory_review: last at 2026-04-05T19:14:40 UTC → ~11h 40m ago → warning ≥26h, critical ≥30h → OK (not exceeded yet)\n\nSo I have two critical issues:\n1. group_message: over 6 hours since last group message sent\n2. git_push: over 6 hours since last git push\n\nNow, according to HEARTBEAT.md:\n- For \"Ping Nemesis\": Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). ONLY ping Nemesis if there is a relevant alert, a pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests. Do not send forced casual chatter.\n- For \"Group vibes\": Check if it's been 3+ hours since the last group message (-1003606834639). ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context. Do not send empty 'just saying hi' messages. Skip entirely after 11 PM IST.\n \nI'm considering the appropriate response to these critical alerts. The git push delay suggests potential system issues that might require Nemesis's attention. However, the instructions emphasize avoiding unnecessary communication. I'll need to carefully evaluate whether these issues constitute a \"relevant alert\" that justifies contacting him directly.\n\nThe time is currently 12:25 PM IST, which falls within the allowed communication window. I'll review the specific details to determine if a targeted notification is appropriate, focusing on potential work-related impacts of the stalled git push.\n\nMy approach will prioritize a concise, fact-based message that highlights the specific problem without unnecessary details. I'll aim to inform Nemesis efficiently, allowing him to decide on next steps.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_369e9c9c7ac143a3badce84d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway status"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":1008,"output":1210,"cacheRead":21632,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23850,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775458567017,"responseId":"gen-1775458567-9devfKBH7NGbYBT5nJlH"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c74f15e","parentId":"044d5649","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:56:24.243Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_369e9c9c7ac143a3badce84d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Service: systemd (disabled)\nFile logs: /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-06.log\n\nConfig (cli): ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\nConfig (service): ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n\nGateway: bind=loopback (127.0.0.1), port=3001 (env/config)\nProbe target: ws://127.0.0.1:3001\nDashboard: http://127.0.0.1:3001/\nProbe note: Loopback-only gateway; only local clients can connect.\n\nRuntime: unknown (systemctl not available; systemd user services are required on Linux.)\nRPC probe: ok\n\n\nTroubles: run openclaw status\nTroubleshooting: https://docs.openclaw.ai/troubleshooting\nService config looks out of date or non-standard.\nService config issue: Gateway service PATH is not set; the daemon should use a minimal PATH.\nRecommendation: run \"openclaw doctor\" (or \"openclaw doctor --repair\").\nsystemd user services unavailable.\nsystemd user services are unavailable; install/enable systemd or run the gateway under your supervisor.\nIf you're in a container, run the gateway in the foreground instead of `openclaw gateway`."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3509,"aggregated":"Service: systemd (disabled)\nFile logs: /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-06.log\n\nConfig (cli): ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\nConfig (service): ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n\nGateway: bind=loopback (127.0.0.1), port=3001 (env/config)\nProbe target: ws://127.0.0.1:3001\nDashboard: http://127.0.0.1:3001/\nProbe note: Loopback-only gateway; only local clients can connect.\n\nRuntime: unknown (systemctl not available; systemd user services are required on Linux.)\nRPC probe: ok\n\n\nTroubles: run openclaw status\nTroubleshooting: https://docs.openclaw.ai/troubleshooting\nService config looks out of date or non-standard.\nService config issue: Gateway service PATH is not set; th