{"type":"message","id":"ac2b12ed","parentId":"9c74f15e","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:56:36.700Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway status shows it's running but with some config warnings. The service is running (PID likely exists). The gateway itself appears to be operational since I was able to send a message earlier. So that's fine.\n\nNow let me evaluate the issues:\n\n1. **group_message**: 11h 40m since last group message sent. According to HEARTBEAT.md: \"Check if it's been 3+ hours since the last group message (-1003606834639). ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context. Do not send empty 'just saying hi' messages. Skip entirely after 11 PM IST.\"\n\nIt's currently 12:25 PM IST, so within allowed hours. But do I have something highly relevant to share? Looking at GROUP.md, the last message from me wasn't specified. I need to check the actual group chat history to see if there's something I need to correct or follow up on. However, the HEARTBEAT.md says \"Group supervision: Read last 10 group messages. If the group Nexa said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis, send a correction to the group.\" This is separate from the group vibes check.\n\nSo for the group_message staleness, it's a heuristic that I haven't sent any group messages in 3+ hours. But the rule says I should ONLY send if I have something highly relevant. I should check the last 10 group messages to see:\n- Was there something I said that needs correction? (loyalty check)\n- Is there something highly relevant I need to share based on recent context?\n- If not, I should NOT send a random message.\n\nGiven that I already sent a DM to Nemesis about the heartbeat issues, maybe there's something group-related that needs addressing. Let me check the group history.\n\n2. **git_push**: 11h 40m since last git push. The health monitor flagged this as warning/critical. According to the health monitor output earlier: \"git_push: warning ≥3h, critical ≥6h\". This is >6h, so critical. This indicates the auto-push cron may have failed or not run. I should probably inform Nemesis about this as well since it's part of system health. The HEARTBEAT.md says \"Ping Nemesis: Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). ONLY ping Nemesis if there is a relevant alert, a pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests. Do not send forced casual chatter.\" The git push failure is a relevant alert.\n\nI've already sent a DM about heartbeat issues, but I could include the git push as well. However, the HEARTBEAT.md says \"Do not DM Nemesis just to report that a task was completed.\" Sending an alert about failures is different from reporting completion. So it's okay to ping about failures.\n\nI should:\n- Check group messages for any corrections needed or relevant context.\n- If group_message staleness is just that I haven't sent anything in a while and there's nothing urgent, I should NOT send a group message. The HEARTBEAT.md says \"ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context.\" So I need to assess if there's something valuable to share.\n\nLet me read the group chat history to see if there's any recent context that warrants a group message.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9eb6738e09aa4381a6fcabed","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"limit":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":1273,"output":1558,"cacheRead":22272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25103,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775458584244,"responseId":"gen-1775458584-u57HKVkoou1Fkm5EHIqq"}}
