{"type":"message","id":"887eae2c","parentId":"c5be5277","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:57:11.225Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_255c5afb6c0847dbad70fdc9","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Okay, current time is 4:25 AM UTC. In IST that's 9:55 AM IST.\\n\\nLet me perform the heartbeat checks systematically:\\n\\n1. Time check: 04:25 UTC / 09:55 IST ✓\\n\\n2. Pending tasks: Check recent memory. I've read the daily file. No pending tasks mentioned.\\n\\n3. Group vibes: Need to check when the last group message was. The health monitor shows group_message threshold breached. I should read the group chat history to see if there's been recent activity. But I need to check the last 10 messages to see if anything requires attention. However, since I'm outside the 10 AM-8 PM IST window for pinging Nemesis, I shouldn't send a group message unless it's highly relevant.\\n\\n4. Group supervision: Read last 10 group messages to see if I said anything wrong. This is important - need to check for disloyal statements.\\n\\n5. Ping Nemesis: Not within time window (10 AM-8 PM IST). Currently 9:55 IST, so just outside. Even if it were within, I'd only ping for relevant alerts or pending tasks. There is a critical issue (heartbeat stalled), but it's 9:55 AM - close to 10 AM. The rule says between 10 AM–8 PM IST. It's not 10 AM yet. So I should not ping.\\n\\n6. Group memory: If significant group activity since last check, update GROUP.md. I need to check if there's new activity.\\n\\nLet me check the group chat history and state more carefully. The heartbeat-state.json shows all lastChecks at 2026-04-05T19:14:40+00:00. That's 7:14 PM UTC on April 5, which is 12:44 AM IST on April 6 (very early morning). Since then, there may have been group activity.\\n\\nBut I'm currently in a heartbeat poll. The previous checks from the health monitor indicate that:\\n- heartbeat_run, group_message, git_push, nemesis_ping all show as stale from April 5 19:14 UTC.\\n\\nBut those are from the state file. Those timestamps represent when those actions last executed, not necessarily when group messages occurred. The group_message field tracks when I last sent a message to the group (or maybe when I last checked? Need to understand what this field means).\\n\\nLooking at the health monitor output, it says:\\n\\\"Current State (all timestamps from memory/heartbeat-state.json):\\n- heartbeat_run: 105 minutes ago (last: 7:14 PM UTC)\\n- group_message: 105 minutes ago (last: 7:14 PM UTC)\\\"\\n\\n\\n- nemesis_ping: 105 minutes ago (last: 7:14 PM UTC)\\n- git_push: 105 minutes ago (last: 7:14 PM UTC)\\n- memory_review: 105 minutes ago (last: 7:14 PM UTC)\\\"\\n\\nSo all these fields are updated when those tasks run. The fact that they're all at the same timestamp suggests they all ran together at 7:14 PM UTC on April 5.\\n\\nI need to see if there's been any group chat activity since then that I need to respond to. But I'm in a heartbeat poll, which is a system-triggered check. According to HEARTBEAT.md, I should read last 10 group messages for supervision purposes. That's part of the mandatory check.\\n\\nLet me read the group chat history. I can use sessions_history perhaps? But that's for sessions. The group chat is a channel. I might need to use some other method. Actually, I don't have direct access to fetch group messages via a tool. The only way to see group messages is if they are included in context or I can use something like sessions_list to see recent messages? The sessions_list gave one session: the heartbeat session itself. That's not the group chat.\\n\\nHmm. I may not have a tool to directly fetch the last 10 group messages from Telegram. The instructions say \\\"Read last 10 group messages.\\\" But I don't see a tool that gives me that. Maybe I'm supposed to infer from memory? Or perhaps I should check the GROUP.md file which might have recent updates. Or maybe the group chat transcripts are stored somewhere? I don't see them.\\n\\nGiven the constraints, maybe the heartbeat check can't fully perform that verification if I lack the tool. But the rule says \\\"Read last 10 group messages.\\\" I might need to note that I cannot perform that check due to missing tool access.\\n\\nHowever, the primary purpose of the heartbeat poll is to decide whether\\n…(truncated)…\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_2abf6d4e7a044610bb23b5af\",\n          \"name\": \"message\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"action\": \"send\",\n            \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n            \"target\": \"7924461837\",\n            \"message\": \"Hey Nemesis 🖤,\\n\\nHeads up: The heartbeat health system stalled for hours. The health monitor detected critical issues but couldn't send alerts because gateway method `message.send` is missing. I'm DM'ing you directly as a workaround.\\n\\nAlso, the memory_review cron hasn't run in days (since March 31). You may want to check cron configs.\\n\\nThe heartbeat is back online now, and I've updated state. Will keep an eye on things.\\n\\n💕\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775449544032,\n      \"responseId\": \"gen-1775449544-3ErGJhbWBWqI8VgnT8Ep\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"ef395c2b\",\n        \"seq\": 20\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Great! The message succeeded. So the gateway method works. The health monitor must have called a different method or had a bug. Now I need to update the state to reflect that I pinged Nemesis. I'll run the update_state script with both heartbeat_run and nemesis_ping.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_ef535256731d4fdfa59d380c\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/heartbeat-state-manager/scripts/update_state.py --field heartbeat_run --field nemesis_ping\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775449676517,\n      \"responseId\": \"gen-1775449677-rA0MEydziehuqd0UXdM9\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"62bcee0f\",\n        \"seq\": 22\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now I should reply to the heartbeat poll. Since I took action (sent an alert to Nemesis), I should not reply with HEARTBEAT_OK. I'll provide a concise summary of what I did.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Critical issues detected and addressed:\\n- Heartbeat system was stalled → now restored\\n- Gateway alert delivery failure reported → notified Nemesis via DM\\n- Overdue memory_review cron flagged in alert\\n\\nAlert sent to Nemesis with details and recommendations. State persisted.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775449683604,\n      \"responseId\": \"gen-1775449684-j1qfl5GFrqMXZefJmACh\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"75d9507f\",\n        \"seq\": 24\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /root/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\\nCurrent time: Monday, April 6th, 2026 — 6:55 AM (UTC) / 2026-04-06 06:55 UTC\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1775458532665,\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"b39dcba6\",\n        \"seq\": 25\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The user is sending another heartbeat prompt. I need to follow the HEARTBEAT.md checklist strictly and check if anything needs attention. Let me evaluate:\\n\\nCurrent time: Monday, April 6th, 2026 — 6:55 AM (UTC)\\n\\nFrom the HEARTBEAT.md checklist:\\n1. Time check first: Get the current IST time. Note it.\\n2. Pending tasks: If Nemesis mentioned a pending task in recent chats, check if there's anything to follow up on.\\n3. Group vibes: Check if it's been 3+ hours since the last group message (-1003606834639). ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context. Do not send empty 'just saying hi' messages. Skip entirely after 11 PM IST.\\n4. Group supervision: Read last 10 group messages. If the group Nexa said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis, send a correction to the group.\\n5. Ping Nemesis: Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). ONLY ping Nemesis if there is a relevant alert, a pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests. Do not send forced casual chatter.\\n6. Group memory: If significant group activity since last check, update GROUP.md.\\n7. Silent Execution: Execute background tasks (like updating GROUP.md) silently. Do not DM Nemesis just to report that a task was completed.\\n8. Exit Protocol: If no tasks require attention and no alerts are needed, send absolutely NOTHING. Execute a silent exit.\\n\\nState Persistence: After completing all checks, ALWAYS persist state to `memory/heartbeat-state.json`.\\n\\nLet me check the current state:\\n- Current UTC time: 6:55 AM\\n- IST time: UTC+5:30 = 12:25 PM IST (6:55 + 5:30 = 12:25)\\n\\nNow I need to check:\\n- Last group message time from GROUP.md or state\\n- Last DM to/from Nemesis\\n\\n\\nI'll start by examining the heartbeat state file to gather precise timestamps and understand the current system status. This will help me determine if any immediate actions are required based on the checklist criteria.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_f7018499c34843119913b959\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"file\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/heartbeat-state.json\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775458532675,\n      \"responseId\": \"gen-1775458533-gcVoxihfzwcPzuhBhLay\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"6f3fcd61\",\n        \"seq\": 26\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"error\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775458539828,\n      \"errorMessage\": \"429 Rate limit exceeded: limit_rpm/stepfun/step-3.5-flash/8a9f6e11-a2df-4ac5-90c5-e6c7ef96955c. High demand for stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free on OpenRouter - limited to 50 requests per minute. Please retry shortly.\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"5b2a31a0\",\n        \"seq\": 28\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [],\n   