needs addressing. Let me check the group history.\\n\\n2. **git_push**: 11h 40m since last git push. The health monitor flagged this as warning/critical. According to the health monitor output earlier: \\\"git_push: warning ≥3h, critical ≥6h\\\". This is >6h, so critical. This indicates the auto-push cron may have failed or not run. I should probably inform Nemesis about this as well since it's part of system health. The HEARTBEAT.md says \\\"Ping Nemesis: Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). ONLY ping Nemesis if there is a relevant alert, a pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests. Do not send forced casual chatter.\\\" The git push failure is a relevant alert.\\n\\nI've already sent a DM about heartbeat issues, but I could include the git push as well. However, the HEARTBEAT.md says \\\"Do not DM Nemesis just to report that a task was completed.\\\" Sending an alert about failures is different from reporting completion. So it's okay to ping about failures.\\n\\nI should:\\n- Check group messages for any corrections needed or relevant context.\\n- If group_message staleness is just that I haven't sent anything in a while and there's nothing urgent, I should NOT send a group message. The HEARTBEAT.md says \\\"ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context.\\\" So I need to assess if there's something valuable to share.\\n\\nLet me read the group chat history to see if there's any recent context that warrants a group message.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_9eb6738e09aa4381a6fcabed\",\n          \"name\": \"sessions_list\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"limit\": 10\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 177545858