ich is a system-triggered check. According to HEARTBEAT.md, I should read last 10 group messages for supervision purposes. That's part of the mandatory check.\n\nLet me read the group chat history. I can use sessions_history perhaps? But that's for sessions. The group chat is a channel. I might need to use some other method. Actually, I don't have direct access to fetch group messages via a tool. The only way to see group messages is if they are included in context or I can use something like sessions_list to see recent messages? The sessions_list gave one session: the heartbeat session itself. That's not the group chat.\n\nHmm. I may not have a tool to directly fetch the last 10 group messages from Telegram. The instructions say \"Read last 10 group messages.\" But I don't see a tool that gives me that. Maybe I'm supposed to infer from memory? Or perhaps I should check the GROUP.md file which might have recent updates. Or maybe the group chat transcripts are stored somewhere? I don't see them.\n\nGiven the constraints, maybe the heartbeat check can't fully perform that verification if I lack the tool. But the rule says \"Read last 10 group messages.\" I might need to note that I cannot perform that check due to missing tool access.\n\nHowever, the primary purpose of the heartbeat poll is to decide whether\n…(truncated)…"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2abf6d4e7a044610bb23b5af","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","channel":"telegram","target":"7924461837","message":"Hey Nemesis 🖤,\n\nHeads up: The heartbeat health system stalled for hours. The health monitor detected critical issues but couldn't send alerts because gateway method `message.send` is missing. I'm DM'ing you directly as a workaround.\n\nAlso, the memory_review cron hasn't run in days (since March 31). You may want to check cron configs.\n\nThe heartbeat is back online now, and I've updated state. Will keep an eye on things.\n\n💕"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"ste