ady alerted Nemesis via DM. That should be sufficient.\n\nI should persist state and then exit. But note: The health monitor output says \"Alert Delivery: Failed to send notifications (gateway method error: `message.send` unknown)\". But I was able to use message.send earlier successfully. So maybe the health monitor script is using a different method or the gateway config is inconsistent. However, I don't need to fix that now.\n\nGiven that I've already addressed the alerts, and there's no further action needed per the checklist (no pending tasks, no group corrections needed, no need to ping again), I should reply HEARTBEAT_OK after persisting state.\n\nBut wait: The HEARTBEAT.md says \"After completing all checks above, ALWAYS persist state to `memory/heartbeat-state.json`.\" So I must run the update_state script. I already did that after my previous DM. But the heartbeat poll that triggered this is a new instance. So I need to persist state again after completing this check (even if no action taken) to refresh the heartbeat_run timestamp.\n\nThus, I will:\n- Run update_state.py --field heartbeat_run\n- Then reply HEARTBEAT_OK\n\nBut careful: The state file currently shows:\n  \"heartbeat_run\": \"2026-04-06T06:26:27.647550+00:00\"\nAnd \"nemesis_ping\": \"2026-04-06T04:28:03.587157+00:00\"\nI haven't updated since my DM. Actually I updated at 06:59:08, so the state should have a newer timestamp for nemesis_ping. But let's check the current state file again after my last update.\n\nI used `exec` to run update_state at 06:59:08. That should have updated both heartbeat_run and nemesis_ping. The file I read earlier before sending the DM showed:\n```\n\"heartbeat_run\": \"2026-04-05T19:14:40+00:00\",\n```\nBut after my updates, the timestamps changed. However, I read the file before my updates? Actually sequence: I read state -> saw old timestamps -> sent DM -> then ran update_state. Then I sent another message? Actually I sent DM about git_push, then ran update_state