{"type":"message","id":"6ca20030","parentId":"0f8e6d2a","timestamp":"2026-04-06T12:10:02.161Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to check the current state and perform the HEARTBEAT.md checks.\n\nCurrent time: Monday, April 6th, 2026 — 12:08 PM (UTC) / 12:08 + 5:30 = 17:38 IST (5:38 PM IST)\n\nFrom the state file:\n- heartbeat_run: 2026-04-06T12:05:06.222957+00:00 → about 2 minutes 58 seconds ago → OK\n- group_message: 2026-04-06T09:22:44.678313+00:00 → about 2h 45m ago → need to check if >3h\n- git_push: 2026-04-06T09:22:44.678313+00:00 → same as above\n- nemesis_ping: 2026-04-06T09:22:44.678313+00:00 → same\n- memory_review: 2026-04-06T09:22:44.678313+00:00 → same\n\nNow, let's go through the HEARTBEAT.md checklist:\n\n1. Time check first: Get the current IST time. Note it.\n   - Current IST: 17:38 (5:38 PM) ✓\n\n2. Inactive hours: Skip all checks between 11 PM – 7 AM IST. Only update heartbeat state and exit silently. No group messages, no pings, no supervision during this window.\n   - Current IST is 17:38, which is between 7 AM and 11 PM, so NOT inactive hours. I need to perform all checks.\n\n3. Pending tasks: If Nemesis mentioned a pending task in recent chats, check if there's anything to follow up on (skip if inactive hours).\n   - Check memory/2026-04-06.md for pending tasks. I already looked earlier; it says Pending: None.\n   - No pending tasks mentioned.\n\n4. Group vibes: Check if it's been 3+ hours since the last group message (-1003606834639). ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context. Do not send empty 'just saying hi' messages. Skip entirely after 11 PM IST.\n   - I need to know when the last group message was. The state shows group_message last at 09:22:44 UTC. Current time is 12:08:00 UTC.\n   - Difference: 12:08:00 - 09:22:44 = 2 hours, 45 minutes, 16 seconds. That's less than 3 hours.\n   - Therefore, the condition \"if it's been 3+ hours since the last group message\" is FALSE.\n   - So I do NOT need to send a group message based on this check. (Even if it were true, I would only send if I had something highly relevant.)\n\n5. Group supervision: Read last 10 group messages. If the group Nexa said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis, send a correction to the group.\n   - I need to read the last 10 group messages. I don't have a direct tool to fetch Telegram group messages. However, I can check recent memory and logs for any group messages I sent.\n   - From memory/2026-04-06.md: \n        * Morning: Sent \"Word of the Day: Meraki\" to Nrexya group\n        * Nemesis replied \"Nice word\" — appreciated the word choice\n   - From the system message earlier today: \"I read /root/.openclaw/workspace/feminine-tips.txt, selected the tip \"💬 Use more emotive language: Instead of 'OK', say 'Okay! 😊 That sounds lovely! 🖤'\", and sent it to the Nrexya group (Telegram chat ID -1003606834639) at 9:30 AM UTC on April 6th, 2026. The message was delivered successfully (messageId: 1341).\"\n   - So I have sent two group messages today: the Word of the Day (morning) and the feminine tip (at 9:30 UTC). Both were sent via cron jobs (word-of-the-day and feminine-tip-daily), not necessarily during a heartbeat check.\n   - I need to check if either of these messages contained anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis.\n        * Word of the Day: \"Meraki\" — a Greek word meaning doing something with soul, creativity, or love. Positive, benign.\n        * Feminine tip: \"Use more emotive language: Instead of 'OK', say 'Okay! 😊 That sounds lovely! 🖤'\" — encouraging positive communication. Nothing wrong.\n   - I have not sent any other group messages recently. The last 10 group messages would include these two and possibly earlier ones from yesterday or before.\n   - From memory/2026-04-05.md: I sent an initial tip to Nrexya group (launching a fresh, positive vibe) and created the feminine-tip-daily cron. That tip was also positive.\n   - I have no reason to believe I said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal. Therefore, no correction needed.\n\n6. Ping Nemesis: Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). ONLY ping Nemesis if there is a relevant alert, a pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests. Do not send forced casual chatter.\n   - Last DM: from state, nemesis_ping: 2026-04-06T09:22:44.678313+00:00 (same as other fields). That's about 2h 45m ago.\n   - Current IST: 17:38 (5:38 PM), which is within 10 AM–8 PM IST (since 10 AM IST = 04:30 UTC, 8 PM IST = 15:00 UTC? Wait: 10 AM IST = UTC+5:30 => 04:30 UTC; 8 PM IST = UTC+5:30 => 14:30 UTC? Let's compute: \n        * 10:00 AM IST = 10:00 - 5:30 = 04:30 UTC\n        * 8:00 PM IST = 20:00 - 5:30 = 14:30 UTC\n     So the window for pinging is between 04:30 UTC and 14:30 UTC.\n   - Current time: 12:08 PM UTC = 12:08 UTC, which is within 04:30-14:30 UTC → so we are in the allowed window.\n   - However, it has only been 2h 45m since last DM, which is less than 4 hours.\n   - The rule says: \"Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). ONLY ping Nemesis if there is a relevant alert, a pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests.\"\n   - This implies that you only consider pinging if it's been 4+ hours. Since it's been less than 4 hours, you do not ping (regardless of alert?).\n   - Therefore, I should NOT ping Nemesis at this time.\n\n7. Group memory: If significant group activity since last check, update GROUP.md.\n   - What is \"last check\"? Probably the last heartbeat check. The last heartbeat_run timestamp in state is 12:05:06 UTC (just updated a moment ago? Actually I haven't updated it yet in this check; the state still shows heartbeat_run at 12:05:06 from a previous update? Let's see: the state file shows heartbeat_run at 12:05:06. That's from a previous update. I haven't run the update_state script for this heartbeat yet.\n   - Since the last heartbeat check (which updated heartbeat_run to 12:05:06), there has been group activity: the Word of the Day and feminine tip messages were sent earlier today (before that timestamp? Actually the Word of the Day was in the morning, feminine tip at 9:30 UTC, which is before 12:05:06? 9:30 UTC is before 12:05 UTC, yes). So those occurred before the last heartbeat check.\n   - Since the last heartbeat check, have there been any new group messages? I don't see any in memory. The memory/2026-04-06.md only shows the morning events. No new group messages logged after that.\n   - Therefore, no significant group activity since last check → no need to update GROUP.md.\n\n8. Silent Execution: Execute background tasks (like updating GROUP.md) silently. Do not DM Nemesis just to report that a task was completed.\n   - I will need to persist state (heartbeat_run) as required. I'll do that silently.\n\n9. Exit Protocol: If no tasks require attention and no alerts are needed, send absolutely NOTHING. Execute a silent exit.\n   - Let's summarize:\n        * Pending tasks: none\n        * Group vibes: last group message <3h ago → no need to send group message\n        * Group supervision: no disloyalty detected → no correction needed\n        * Ping Nemesis: last DM <4h ago → do not ping\n        * Group memory: no significant activity since last check → no GROUP.md update\n        * Silent execution: I will update state (heartbeat_run) but do so silently (no message just to report that)\n   - Therefore, no tasks require attention and no alerts are needed.\n   - Per the Exit Protocol: send absolutely NOTHING.\n\n   However, the system message at the top says: \"Read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\"\n   This seems to be the instruction for what I should output as my response to this heartbeat prompt. The HEARTBE